Mary J. Blige, Jamie Foxx, and Jennifer Hudson were among the winners at the
21st annual Soul Train Music Awards, held March 10 in Pasadena, California.
Mary J. Blige took the Best Female Album award for The Breakthrough, while
Jamie Foxx brought home Best Male Album honors for Unpredictable. Former
American Idol castoff Jennifer Hudson continued her Cinderella story, winning
the Entertainer Of The Year award for her supporting role in the movieÂ 
Dreamgirls. She also received an Academy Award and an NAACP Image Award for her
role.
